[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T17:33:55+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Half-Life 2 featuring a close up of character Alyx Vance.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yMyz_Zk_75ObEMdBBaLq5KQ3l0w=/80x0:944x576/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73726390/ss_18841cb9a8fc2cf67039317b601d10c4059b6fa8.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Valve</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UfUYJS\"><em>Half-Life 2 </em>is getting a <a href=\"https://www.half-life.com/en/halflife2/20th\">major update</a> in celebration of the classic title\u2019s 20th anniversary. In addition to Steam Workshop support directly within the game, Valve has fixed bugs and restored some content, added new graphics settings, updated gamepad controls, and a whole lot more. You\u2019ll also be able to get the game for free <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/app/220/HalfLife_2/\">on Steam</a> for free through November 18th at 1PM ET. After that, it will cost $9.99.</p>\n<p id=\"t9eWyp\">Valve is also now including the Episode One and Episode ", "id": 1524366, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297691/half-life-2-20th-anniversary-update-documentary", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Half-Life 2 is getting a huge 20th anniversary update", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T16:51:39+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing ESPN\u2019s FACTS avatar\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ETlCu0m5rGxTg8c5iyipoESmFfE=/125x0:1475x900/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73726311/espn_facts.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: ESPN</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"DuIi6W\">ESPN is testing <a href=\"https://www.espnfrontrow.com/2024/11/generative-ai-avatar-facts-announced-at-4th-annual-espn-edge-conference/\">an AI-generated avatar</a> with the Saturday college football show <em>SEC Nation</em>. Dubbed FACTS, it\u2019s going to be \u201c...promoting education and fun around sports analytics\u201d with information drawn from ESPN Analytics, which includes data like the Football Power Index (FPI), player and team statistics, and game schedules. We haven\u2019t seen the avatar in action, but it sounds like a bot-ified version of stats encyclopedia <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/23/sports/howie-schwab-dead.html\">Howie Schwab</a>, who was ESPN\u2019s first statistician ", "id": 1524051, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297606/espn-generative-ai-avatar-facts", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "ESPN is testing a generative AI avatar called \u2018FACTS\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T15:57:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Google Gemini logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/l1svhsqfVNlxEn7KfHm37miUs3I=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73726166/STK255_Google_Gemini_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wR6zdb\">Google Workspace is <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2024/11/use-gemini-in-google-docs-to-create-images.html\">rolling out a Gemini-powered AI image generator</a> directly in Google Docs that lets you quickly whip up visuals for your writeups. Essentially, it's a clip art maker that follows in the footsteps of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/10/12/23400270/ai-generated-art-dall-e-microsoft-designer-app-office-365-suite\">Microsoft\u2019s AI-generated art feature</a> in its Office products.</p>\n<p id=\"ZYE65n\">Google\u2019s image generator in Docs is available to paid Workspace accounts that include the Gemini Business,<strong> </strong", "id": 1524052, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297524/google-docs-gemini-ai-image-generator-clip-art", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google will let you make AI clip art for your documents", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T13:52:43+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The 16-inch MacBook Pro with M4 Max (left) next to a 14-inch MacBook Pro with M4 (right) on a green tabletop in a cafe.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/COomJC1rb6kqg5JTetGKymtW2Ks=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725861/247372_MacBook_Pro_M4_ADiBenedetto_0019.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fspE0V\">The new M4 MacBook Pros that launched last month have an unadvertised change with new quantum dot displays, according to display industry analyst Ross Young and <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2024/11/15/apple-quietly-gave-the-m4-macbook-pro-a-quantum-dot-display/\">reported by <em>9to5Mac</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"v2TFY6\"><a href=\"https://x.com/DSCCRoss/status/1857208745014776215\">Young posted on X</a> that Apple is adopting quantum dot displays for the first time and that it's using a version of the film that is free of cadmium, which is toxic ", "id": 1523488, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297414/m4-macbook-pro-quantum-dot-display", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The M4 MacBook Pro features a quantum dot display", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T13:44:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Bluesky logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Bj0Mpu_0Jr8ZufOFGYKXcDZGkY8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725834/STK133_BLUESKY__A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6EWi95\">Social network Bluesky, in a post on Friday, says that it has \u201cno intention\u201d of taking user content to train generative AI tools. It made the statement shortly ahead of competitor X implementing its new terms of service that spell out how it can analyze user text and other information to train its generative AI tools.</p>\n<p id=\"h3h2eD\">\u201cA number of artists and creators have made their home on Bluesky, and we hear their concerns with other platforms training on their data,\u201d <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/bsky.app/post/3layuzbto2c2x\">Bluesky says in a post</a>. \u201cWe do not use any of your content to train generative AI, and have no intention of do", "id": 1523489, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297442/bluesky-no-intention-train-generative-ai-posts", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bluesky says it won\u2019t train AI on your posts", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T13:24:26+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Steam logo on a pink background, surrounded by Valve logos.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LeyjxZEzUuyZqs16W7GCt6DanmI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725792/STK139_Stream_Kradtke_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OrgYsf\">US Senator Mark Warner (D-VA) <a href=\"https://www.warner.senate.gov/public/_cache/files/8/4/84b68bc0-e6dc-4ecc-a148-592f9e7a4d1b/F48B5B4549C67C9692B2A787F7A485C57AF2BD64A1DE1154CFE274C3327A6096.241115.warner-valve-steam-content-letter-final.sign-1-.pdf\">has sent a letter to Valve CEO Gabe Newell</a> asking if the company intends to take measures to curtail extremist content on Steam. The letter references <a href=\"https://www.adl.org/resources/report/steam-powered-hate-top-gaming-site-rife-extremism-antisemitism\">a report by the Anti-Defamation League</a> that identified a large number of user accounts and user-created groups \u201cthat g", "id": 1523124, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297364/steam-extremist-content-moderation-us-senator-warner-letter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Senator to Valve: what\u2019s with all the Nazis on Steam?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hand holding Apple\u2019s 2022 iPhone SE at a slight angle.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2Tb-o1k2kjBjqUjZ_XIBb6xYm5s=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725579/ajohnson_221103_5070_0004.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>This could be so much better.</em> | Photo by Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"i87oZp\">We could argue all day about the merits of iOS versus Android, but there\u2019s one thing the Android ecosystem offers that you definitely won\u2019t find from Apple right now: a decent midrange phone. </p>\n<p id=\"QmeLyP\">By \u201cdecent,\u201d I mean something I can enthusiastically recommend. Not \u201cEh, if it\u2019s literally your only option, then it\u2019s fine,\u201d which is how I\u2019ve caveated <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23618862/best-iphone-camera-battery-screen-guide\">my recommendations of the iPhone SE</a> over the past couple of years. Remember the SE? Apple released <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2", "id": 1522772, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24296505/apple-iphone-se-rumors-mac-mini", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The new Mac Mini is great \u2014 now do the\u00a0iPhone\u00a0SE", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T11:22:36+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"cruise vehicle driving in city\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CuAQqS5MzbR-kTD6bfXvlu0gdmo=/0x0:4241x2827/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725499/IAH_Final_Photography___240916___7724.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cruise</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"P6fWIc\">GM\u2019s Cruise will <a href=\"https://www.justice.gov/usao-ndca/pr/cruise-admits-submitting-false-report-influence-federal-investigation-and-agrees-pay\">pay a criminal fine of $500,000 to resolve a federal investigation</a> and accept a deferred prosecution agreement after the company admitted to falsifying a report to the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) \u201cwith the intent to impede, obstruct, or influence the investigation\u201d of a crash where one of its driverless vehicles <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/3/23901233/cruise-crash-hit-run-pedestrian-injury-sf-robotaxi\">struck and dragged a pedestrian in 2023</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"yWFKwH\">N", "id": 1522361, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297248/cruise-robotaxi-criminal-fine-falsify-report-pedestrian", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Cruise fined $500k for submitting a false report after last year\u2019s pedestrian crash", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T11:11:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-QIaz1XovoAhIWqxr6yhdXW0qmA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70693925/Robot_Vacuums_Best_2024.8.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Floor-sweeping robots are only getting better, with new mopping skills, better navigation chops, and more automation, meaning less work for you. We picked the best bots you can buy right now.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22997597/best-robot-vacuum-cleaner\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1522362, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22997597/best-robot-vacuum-cleaner", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best robot vacuums ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T10:58:52+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Facebook logo surrounded by blue circles\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qNh3dcb7Rpsprx4O2uWz4MfGq3o=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725433/STK040_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_1_facebook.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"A7lg9D\">Facebook <a href=\"https://creators.facebook.com/introducing-views-to-simplify-content\">is making</a> \u201cviews\u201d its primary metric to measure the performance of content, bringing it <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215398/instagram-primary-metric-views\">in line with Instagram metrics</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"hHY9Ff\">Views will be measured not just on video content but also on photos, text posts, and more. When Instagram head Adam Mosseri <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/C-X7FtePYyj/\">announced</a> the switch to views this summer, he said that having one consistent metric across the platform would make i", "id": 1522363, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297255/facebook-metrics-views-instagram", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Facebook is changing its primary metric to \u2018views\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T10:51:40+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JtqxLQU3ZLAewhCAko6QFM0j_-U=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73725419/STK156_Instagram_threads_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yRPsFP\">Threads is testing a way to create custom feeds for certain profiles or topics, <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@zuck/post/DCZXY14P2Yy?hl=en\">Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg announced</a> on Friday. The upcoming feature should make it easier to keep tabs on different interests, such as your favorite sports team or even technology-related news.</p>\n<p id=\"VpADJA\">It sounds similar to the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296490/meta-threads-15-million-adam-mosseri-bluesky\">custom feeds feature Bluesky</a> rolled out last year \u2014 but Threads\u2019 version seems <em>a lot</em> simpler. To create a custom feed, just search and tap into a topic. From there, select t", "id": 1522364, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297313/threads-custom-feeds-test", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads is testing custom feeds for your favorite topics", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-15T10:51:19+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of Elon Musk in a tuxedo making